Vendored/ported AOSP components (pin: tools-base 14c65dad2cbdc26198c66375d4e0cef5269436e0,
recorded in third_party/PINNED.txt):

1. On-device LiveEdit bytecode interpreter — engine/src/main/resources/dev/hotreload/interp.dex
   Built from tools-base deploy/agent/runtime {interpreter, liveedit, liveedit/backported} plus
   instrument/ReflectionHelpers, compiled and dexed unchanged except for build-time source-level
   jarjar of ASM and trivial annotation/Proxies stubs (see the sibling interp.dex.PROVENANCE and
   scripts/build-interp-dex.sh). Copyright (C) The Android Open Source Project. Apache-2.0.

2. Interpreter JNI dispatch natives — runtime-client/lib/src/main/cpp/interpreter_jni.cpp
   Port of tools-base deploy/agent/native/jni_dispatch/jni_dispatch.cc (the invokespecial* family
   and monitor enter/exit natives that com.android.tools.deploy.interpreter.JNI declares).
   Copyright (C) The Android Open Source Project. Apache-2.0. The per-file header records the
   differences from the original.

3. Host-side priming transform — engine/src/main/kotlin/dev/hotreload/engine/StubTransform.kt
   A Kotlin/ASM re-implementation, on JVM `.class` bytes, of the semantics of tools-base
   deploy/agent/native/transform/stub_transform.cc (the LiveEdit stub prologue / $liveEditBytecode
   field / stubConstructor tail). Derived from that Apache-2.0 source.

The unbox-flag constants in interpreter_jni.cpp are kept byte-identical to AOSP's
AndroidEval.java by design; do not alter them independently.
